---
title: Za'atar-Roasted Root Veggies with Farro, Yogurt, and an Herb Gremolata
description: We don’t believe in monogamy when it comes to spices. We like to sample the whole wide world of seasonings, jumping from one spicy affair to the next. So take it from us when we say that za’atar is the perfect ingredient for your adventurous side: this Middle Eastern blend contains a bazaar’s worth of herbs and aromatics, from thyme and marjoram to sesame and sumac. In this recipe, it’s sprinkled on warm carrots and parsnips, but we think you’ll wanna spread the love and put it on everything.
